<br>
I am a 61 mage who built my entire style of play around the T-rod. The ONLY element of the nerf that I am referring to here is SOLO power in pre-PoP environment. I am fully aware that no mere pet can replace what the T-rod meant to a raid, however I am not talking about that aspect of it's power here. I am referring to the self regen of mana that the t-rod allowed when combined with regen/rune items, for use when soloing.<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>edit: I realized after I wrote this that some rune items matched with old t-rod can never be equaled for solo mana regen, however as that is such a tiny percentage of the mage population, I don't think its relevant to the discussion here (esp as I dont have a rune item hehe). </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Ok on to the matter at hand. As I had posted before, I had compared the Ward of Xegony's tanking power compared to the Epic in Fungus Grove. My method of testing was simply to stack two shrooms on the pet and then gauge tanking ability. In this test the epic outperformed the Air pet, however I feel that was due more to its procs (no proccing weapons on Air) and its DS (only Cadeau on Air).<br>
<br>
Now I decided today to see how Air would perform in a solo XP scenario in FG. I was hoping that it's regenerative rate would significantly offset my now severely lowered mana regeneration rate.<br>
<br>
I was right.<br>
<br>
The setup:<br>
In FG, I was pulling just shrooms, who at 61 are mostly blue still, with some light blues interspersed. The Ward was buffed with BO4, a muzzle of mardu, and Cadeau of Flame. I consider myself to be a slightly better than average equipped 61 mage. I only have a single FT item (FT1) and my int solo is about 253 or so (not maxxed at 260 even with all my int gear on). Please check my magelo profile to compare your own gear.<br>
<br>
I am giddy. I literally feel like I did when I first hit 39 and the pet's HP and regen jumped WAY up. The very first fight I started, I was at 30m, so I just tagged the shroom with burst of fire and let the Ward go at it. Ward finished the fight at approx 50% health left. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> It took all of 60 seconds to fully regenerate this damage.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> For the next 5 fights my mana bar went in one direction, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>UP</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. By then end of the fifth fight I realized I should be nuking more as my mana bar was now full, so I accelerated my pulls.<br>
<br>
All told I got a blue bub in AAXP in about 20 minutes, with only 80% xp going to AAXP, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>and I regenerated my mana the whole time</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. I had a net mana GAIN after all those fights, without using anything but TPP. I had NO KEI on, I was just self buffed. I could(and will when I go back) pull significantly faster by just nuking more. I had plenty of mana.<br>
<br>
Post fight thoughts - <br>
If I had blades of walnan or any of the procing weapons, the Air pet would have dominated the epic, due to the fact that it's DPS would have been almost the same, and it's HP is not significantly less against old world blues, plus the fact that it has STUPID regen. I almost feel like giggling as I watch it's HP jump up about 2-3 % every tick. Additionally, it was resisting shroom spells noticeably better than the epic. I wouldn't say it's a HUGE difference in resists, but it is noticeable.<br>
<br>
Looks like the Epic pet, for me at least, is getting relegated to &quot;Emergency Backup Pet&quot; role, since it's a free right click. Oh well, at least the Orb's stats are still awesome.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> SICK SICK SICK REGEN!!! </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Anyways I just wanted to share with everyone this aspect of the 61+ pets (at least Ward of Xegony). For you mages without an epic pet, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>you are going to LOVE this pet!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. For us mages that sank 150+ hours into getting our epic, well look at it this way, at least it's still a good stat item, and it IS a comfort always knowing that you have a decent mana free pet as a backup once you get over 60.<br>
